                "text": "Once per minute, a shadow demon increase its fly speed to 240 feet for 1 round."
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "name": "Shadow Blend",
                "ability_type": "Supernatural",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Su",
                "text": "During any conditions other than bright light, a shadow demon can disappear into the shadows as a move-equivalent action, effectively becoming invisible. Artificial illumination or light spells of 2nd level or lower do not negate this ability."
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "name": "Sunlight Powerlessness",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex",
                "text": "A shadow demon is utterly powerless in bright light or natural sunlight and flees from it. A shadow demon caught in such light cannot attack and can take only a single move or standard action. A shadow demon that is possessing a creature using <i>magic jar </i>is not harmed by sunlight, but if it is struck by a <i>sunbeam </i>or <i>sunburst </i>spell while possessing a creature, the shadow demon is driven out of its host automatically."
            }
